revision.text:
'''Sannō Shrine''' (山王神社) refers to various {{ill|Shinto shrines|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} across Japan based on {{ill|Sannō faith|ja|山王信仰|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* '''Hokkaido and Tōhoku Region''' ''' {{ill|Sannō Shrine (Tomakomai City)|ja|山王神社 (苫小牧市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Located adjacent to Hokkaido University’s experimental forest. In recent years, a large torii gate was damaged by a typhoon, leaving only its base. ''' {{ill|Sannō Shrine (Takahata Town)|ja|山王神社 (高畠町)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Takahata Town|ja|高畠町|12=draft|12=draft}}, Higashiokitama District, Yamagata Prefecture.
* '''Kantō and Kōshin Region''' ''' {{ill|Sannō Shrine (Sakuragawa City)|ja|山王神社 (桜川市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Sakuragawa City|ja|桜川市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Ibaraki Prefecture. ''' {{ill|Sannō Shrine (Edogawa Ward)|ja|山王神社 (江戸川区)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Edogawa Ward|ja|江戸川区|12=draft|12=draft}}, Tokyo Metropolis. ''' {{ill|Sannō Shrine (Hachiōji City)|ja|山王神社 (八王子市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Hachiōji City|ja|八王子市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Tokyo Metropolis. ''' {{ill|Sannō Shrine (Odawara City)|ja|山王神社 (小田原市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Odawara City|ja|小田原市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Kanagawa Prefecture.
* '''Kyushu and Okinawa Region''' ''' {{ill|Sannō Shrine|ja|山王神社 (長崎市)|12=draft|12=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Nagasaki City|ja|長崎市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Nagasaki Prefecture.
{{Disambiguation}}
{{citation needed|Sannō Shrine}}
